&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
The initial port of Clang to produce PNaCl-compatible bitcode is done. Clang can't be used as a replacement of llvm-gcc for now.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
We can't benefit from Clang port w/o the integration with the tools.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
 We need to integrate it with our existing tools (such as utman.sh).

Some integration has been already done by David Meyer. This bug is to track the outstanding issues.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
It's possible to build PNaCl toolchain that contains Clang and does not contain llvm-gcc.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
llvm-gcc can be thrown out. It's not maintained by LLVM team.
